modules.description: This module provides serialization and deserialization functions for the `Bitvec.t` type using the Binprot protocol. It includes operations for measuring size, writing and reading values, and defining shape and type-level protocols. These functions support implementing binable interfaces for existing types without redefining the type, enabling direct integration with Binprot-based systems like network protocols or binary storage formats.

This module implements serialization and deserialization for `Bitvec.t` using the Binprot protocol, enabling efficient binary encoding of bit vectors for storage or transmission. It provides functions to measure size, write to and read from buffers, along with shape and type class instances that support integration with Binprot-based systems. Child modules extend these capabilities to existing types, allowing them to adopt binable interfaces without redefining their structure. Example uses include persisting bit vectors to disk or sending them over network protocols in a compact binary format.
